description:
The following are the most outstanding and distinguishing characteristics of this new cultivar when grown under normal horticultural practices in Andijk, The Netherlands and Hillscheid, Germany.



        1. Small to medium-sized blue-violet, bell-shaped flowers;
        2. Floriferous with the flowers borne well-above the foliage;
        3. An early flowering response;
        4. Deep green and slightly glossy foliage with small, cordate leaves;
        5. A compact, well-branched plant habit; and
        6. A mainly tight and bushy, later partly decumbent growth habit.
